1
00:00:01,140 --> 00:00:12,290
♪

2
00:00:12,290 --> 00:00:14,290
(singing in foreign language)

3
00:00:14,290 --> 00:01:33,250
♪

4
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:37,150
♪

5
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:39,030
One-hundred and forty years ago,

6
00:01:39,030 --> 00:01:42,190
during the turbulent period
at the end of the Tokugawa era,

7
00:01:42,190 --> 00:01:44,290
a samurai named
Battousai the Slasher

8
00:01:44,290 --> 00:01:46,070
lived in Kyoto.

9
00:01:46,070 --> 00:01:47,210
♪

10
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:50,080
Battousai was the
most powerful swordsman

11
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:52,120
who slashed people
in a scene of carnage

12
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:54,270
that cleared the way
to a new era,

13
00:01:54,270 --> 00:01:56,120
the Meiji era.

14
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:58,200
♪

15
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:00,180
But as the disturbances ended,

16
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:02,000
he disappeared.

17
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,170
♪

18
00:02:04,170 --> 00:02:07,010
While his whereabouts
remained a mystery,

19
00:02:07,010 --> 00:02:09,140
the name Battousai
the Slasher

20
00:02:09,140 --> 00:02:12,190
became a legend.

21
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:21,240
♪

22
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:23,210
(wind blowing)

23
00:02:33,260 --> 00:02:36,220
Wait!

24
00:02:36,220 --> 00:02:38,070
Wait.

25
00:02:38,070 --> 00:02:41,240
Battousai the Slasher.

26
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:43,180
Who?

27
00:02:43,180 --> 00:02:45,260
I have finally found you.

28
00:02:45,260 --> 00:02:48,140
You're a gentle-looking man,
Battousai the Slasher.

29
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:49,250
Huh?

30
00:02:49,250 --> 00:02:51,270
(yelling)

31
00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:57,220
What in the...

32
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:59,190
(yelling)

33
00:03:01,694 --> 00:03:02,220
Ah!

34
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:03,220
Huh?

35
00:03:03,220 --> 00:03:05,190
(groaning)

36
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:10,110
So are you really
the legendary Slasher?

37
00:03:10,110 --> 00:03:14,000
I've heard stories that you
killed three people at once.

38
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:16,270
No, I'm a wanderer.

39
00:03:16,270 --> 00:03:18,230
All I am is a
wandering swordsman

40
00:03:18,230 --> 00:03:20,050
with no place to go.

41
00:03:20,050 --> 00:03:23,030
Do you think I can slash
anyone with this sword?

42
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:27,040
(sword unsheathing)

43
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,020
Hey, what is this?

44
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:29,160
The edge is reversed.

45
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:30,270
It's a reversed-edge sword.

46
00:03:30,270 --> 00:03:32,140
Why is the edge reversed?

47
00:03:32,140 --> 00:03:35,000
This sword can't slash people.

48
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,100
(groaning)

49
00:03:36,100 --> 00:03:38,270
And you don't see any
evidence of slashing, right?

50
00:03:38,270 --> 00:03:40,050
(groans)

51
00:03:40,050 --> 00:03:41,260
Actually, it's in
perfect condition.

52
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:44,280
It seems like it's
practically brand new.

53
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:47,070
You know it wasn't
me, don't you?

54
00:03:47,070 --> 00:03:49,040
You could still get hurt!

55
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,200
Battousai appears
every night,

56
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:53,100
testing his sword by
killing innocent people!

57
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,230
If you walk around town
at night carrying a sword,

58
00:03:55,230 --> 00:03:57,110
anybody could make a mistake!

59
00:03:57,110 --> 00:03:58,220
And let me tell you this,

60
00:03:58,220 --> 00:04:00,030
you should know
it's against the law

61
00:04:00,030 --> 00:04:02,090
to carry a sword
in the Meiji era!

62
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:03,190
(high-pitched whistle blows)

63
00:04:03,190 --> 00:04:06,040
And I'm not kidding about this!

64
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:08,010
(whimpering)

65
00:04:11,110 --> 00:04:13,080
(whistling continues)

66
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:19,090
You two are dead meat.

67
00:04:19,090 --> 00:04:20,260
(grunting)

68
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:23,130
♪

69
00:04:23,130 --> 00:04:25,080
My word, I have
never seen anyone

70
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,020
with this kind
of strength before.

71
00:04:27,020 --> 00:04:28,170
It's Battousai!

72
00:04:28,170 --> 00:04:31,000
♪

73
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,080
(yelling)

74
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:44,210
♪

75
00:04:52,050 --> 00:04:53,080
How did you...

76
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,290
It's not a good idea
to start a fight

77
00:04:54,290 --> 00:04:56,180
with a wooden sword.

78
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:57,130
(whistling continues)

79
00:04:57,130 --> 00:04:58,280
It's Battousai!

80
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:01,170
Don't let him
get away this time!

81
00:05:01,170 --> 00:05:03,030
I am Battousai.

82
00:05:03,030 --> 00:05:04,270
Kamiya Kasshin style.

83
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:06,200
Battousai the Slasher!

84
00:05:06,200 --> 00:05:07,190
Wait!

85
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:09,030
Let him go for now.

86
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:11,090
Kamiya Kasshin style
is our style.

87
00:05:11,090 --> 00:05:13,010
He's slandering
my father's dojo

88
00:05:13,010 --> 00:05:15,290
as he murders people.

89
00:05:15,290 --> 00:05:17,160
(sighs)

90
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,240
Boy, is she a
strong-willed woman.

91
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:24,010
(whistling continues)

92
00:05:24,010 --> 00:05:25,280
(birds chirping)

93
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:41,180
Huh?

94
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,070
Ouch!

95
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,170
I almost forgot about Battousai.

96
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:51,290
I wonder what happened.

97
00:05:51,290 --> 00:05:53,080
Oh!

98
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,160
♪

99
00:05:57,190 --> 00:06:00,090
(birds chirping)

100
00:06:00,090 --> 00:06:02,020
I smell miso soup.

101
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:04,040
♪

102
00:06:04,040 --> 00:06:06,150
I'm getting tired
of carrying this thing.

103
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:07,220
Let's just throw it in.

104
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,290
-Okay.
-Hi, kids.

105
00:06:08,290 --> 00:06:11,190
Oh, I wouldn't do
that if I were--ah!

106
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:14,180
♪

107
00:06:14,180 --> 00:06:16,150
Just what's going on out here?

108
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:18,030
Oh, good, you're awake!

109
00:06:18,030 --> 00:06:20,120
Your little sisters
are so cute.

110
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:23,070
We're quickly becoming
the best of friends.

111
00:06:23,070 --> 00:06:24,030
Yeah!

112
00:06:24,030 --> 00:06:25,170
Best friends!

113
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:26,240
I've been cooking breakfast

114
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:28,270
and these two have
been my big helpers.

115
00:06:28,270 --> 00:06:31,020
It tastes pretty good,
would you like some?

116
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,050
Want some?

117
00:06:32,050 --> 00:06:34,210
♪

118
00:06:34,210 --> 00:06:36,280
You really made these
rice balls yourself?

119
00:06:39,060 --> 00:06:41,180
I can't believe what you did.

120
00:06:41,180 --> 00:06:42,210
(coughing)

121
00:06:42,210 --> 00:06:44,100
Wha-wha-what's the matter?

122
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:47,070
It doesn't taste good?

123
00:06:47,070 --> 00:06:50,040
My friend, you cook
better than I do.

124
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:51,240
(descending whistle)

125
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:54,290
(gong ringing)

126
00:06:54,290 --> 00:06:58,030
(birds chirping)

127
00:06:58,030 --> 00:07:00,080
(giggling)

128
00:07:00,080 --> 00:07:01,290
He must have
treated you quickly.

129
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:04,230
I'm happy to see that
the wound has healed nicely.

130
00:07:06,220 --> 00:07:08,110
He certainly doesn't
look like a typical

131
00:07:08,110 --> 00:07:10,220
samurai swordsman, does he?

132
00:07:10,220 --> 00:07:13,040
He's a perfect babysitter
for my grandkids.

133
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,250
(laughing)

134
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:16,120
(sneezes)

135
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,040
Sorry.

136
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,170
So, are you telling me
these cute little girls

137
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:22,290
are not Ms. Kori's
sisters after all?

138
00:07:22,290 --> 00:07:25,160
Right, they are
Dr. Gensai's granddaughters.

139
00:07:25,160 --> 00:07:27,170
I've been the physician
in charge of this dojo

140
00:07:27,170 --> 00:07:29,010
for 30 years.

141
00:07:29,010 --> 00:07:31,030
But ever since Kori's
parents passed away,

142
00:07:31,030 --> 00:07:33,050
I've been more like her father.

143
00:07:33,050 --> 00:07:35,050
Okay, that should do it.

144
00:07:35,050 --> 00:07:37,120
Mr. Wanderer, if you like,
you're welcome to stay

145
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:40,110
at our dojo until you
decide to leave town.

146
00:07:40,110 --> 00:07:42,010
Huh?

147
00:07:42,010 --> 00:07:43,170
You saved my life
and I can tell

148
00:07:43,170 --> 00:07:44,290
you don't have any money.

149
00:07:44,290 --> 00:07:46,200
A generous samurai
would extend to you

150
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:49,110
the same courtesy.

151
00:07:49,110 --> 00:07:50,130
You don't even know me.

152
00:07:50,130 --> 00:07:51,250
Are you sure?

153
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,050
♪

154
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:54,220
You must have had
a difficult past

155
00:07:54,220 --> 00:07:56,110
to be wandering around,

156
00:07:56,110 --> 00:07:57,210
but we don't have
to talk about it

157
00:07:57,210 --> 00:07:59,060
unless you want to.

158
00:07:59,060 --> 00:08:09,160
♪

159
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:12,140
Ms. Kori, are you
the master in this dojo?

160
00:08:12,140 --> 00:08:14,170
Yes, my father
started this school

161
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:16,270
and invented the
Kamiya Kasshin style.

162
00:08:16,270 --> 00:08:18,090
It's not for hurting people,

163
00:08:18,090 --> 00:08:19,280
it's for helping people.

164
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:22,220
Kasshin sword,
that's the idea.

165
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:25,230
I can't believe that killer
is using the Kasshin style name.

166
00:08:25,230 --> 00:08:28,200
Battousai is damaging
my father's ideals.

167
00:08:30,090 --> 00:08:32,040
How could he, it's so wrong!

168
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:33,200
(door opens)

169
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,280
Kori!

170
00:08:35,280 --> 00:08:38,230
Your Kamiya Kasshin students
are ready for their lesson.

171
00:08:38,230 --> 00:08:40,220
Look, I can't beat
Battousai alone,

172
00:08:40,220 --> 00:08:42,140
but I think we can do it
with all the members

173
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:45,130
of the Kamiya dojo.

174
00:08:45,130 --> 00:08:47,020
Thanks for coming, everyone.

175
00:08:47,020 --> 00:08:48,250
Tonight we need
to discuss the--

176
00:08:48,250 --> 00:08:51,050
Well, uh, tell you the truth,

177
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:53,100
we're gonna quit this dojo.

178
00:08:53,100 --> 00:08:54,110
Huh?

179
00:08:54,110 --> 00:08:56,090
Friends are talking
about me behind my back,

180
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:59,210
saying the Kamiya Kasshin
school breeds murderers.

181
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:01,270
I have to quit your dojo
'cause my mom doesn't want me

182
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:04,190
training to be a murderer.

183
00:09:04,190 --> 00:09:06,190
I don't think I can go on.

184
00:09:06,190 --> 00:09:07,200
♪

185
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:09,010
I feel bad.

186
00:09:09,010 --> 00:09:10,250
We were the last
three students you had.

187
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:14,220
I'm sorry, I feel awful, Kori.

188
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,160
-I'm really sorry.
-I'm really sorry.

189
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:36,160
♪

190
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:44,270
I will keep this dojo
alive even if I'm alone.

191
00:09:44,270 --> 00:09:46,240
(fire crackling)

192
00:09:50,070 --> 00:09:51,170
What?

193
00:09:51,170 --> 00:09:53,140
(fire roaring)

194
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:57,200
Hey, you know what, Kenshin?

195
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:59,170
I think she's crying in there.

196
00:09:59,170 --> 00:10:01,220
No, no, I have to be strong.

197
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:03,040
I'll survive.

198
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:04,010
(gasps)

199
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,260
Ms. Kori, what's
going on in there?

200
00:10:11,260 --> 00:10:14,060
Oh my gosh, Kori!

201
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:16,210
(bubbles popping)

202
00:10:16,210 --> 00:10:19,060
(gasps)

203
00:10:19,060 --> 00:10:21,040
Wait, don't drown yourself!

204
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,110
Oh my!

205
00:10:22,110 --> 00:10:24,040
♪

206
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,130
(gasps)

207
00:10:29,210 --> 00:10:31,180
(door creaks, slams)

208
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:36,150
Why don't you think about
what you did overnight?

209
00:10:36,150 --> 00:10:37,120
Okay.

210
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:41,150
Can I ask you one thing?

211
00:10:41,150 --> 00:10:42,140
What is it?

212
00:10:42,140 --> 00:10:43,270
I was wondering
if you remember

213
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:46,040
a certain student
in this dojo.

214
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:48,030
He was left-handed
and had a right thumb

215
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:50,050
that didn't move.

216
00:10:50,050 --> 00:10:52,010
He's the street murderer.

217
00:10:52,010 --> 00:10:53,120
But...

218
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:56,020
Are you saying that killer
was a student here?

219
00:10:56,020 --> 00:10:57,050
Don't you understand,

220
00:10:57,050 --> 00:10:59,040
the Kamiya Kasshin style
is the philosophy

221
00:10:59,040 --> 00:11:00,120
of non-violence.

222
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,240
There's no way
one of our students

223
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,130
would kill anybody!

224
00:11:03,130 --> 00:11:04,270
You're talking about Battousai,

225
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:06,230
a bloodthirsty, evil killer!

226
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:09,030
I will defend this
dojo's name with my life.

227
00:11:09,030 --> 00:11:11,090
That's the only way to
honor my father's memory

228
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:14,280
and to keep our dojo alive.

229
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,250
Your father...

230
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,230
he would not want you
to defend anything

231
00:11:18,230 --> 00:11:20,250
if you had to lose your life.

232
00:11:20,250 --> 00:11:22,260
No father would want that.

233
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:26,100
Your late father's
wish would be...

234
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,190
he'd want you to be
safe and happy.

235
00:11:28,190 --> 00:11:29,170
Hm?

236
00:11:32,130 --> 00:11:33,190
You are just a wanderer,

237
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:36,230
what do you know about how
he would have felt anyway?

238
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:45,090
(dog barking)

239
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:51,240
(whimpering)

240
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:02,210
Your late father's
wish would be...

241
00:12:02,210 --> 00:12:05,100
he'd want you to
be safe and happy.

242
00:12:05,100 --> 00:12:06,220
Huh?

243
00:12:06,220 --> 00:12:07,260
Ah!

244
00:12:07,260 --> 00:12:20,140
♪

245
00:12:20,140 --> 00:12:21,210
Hello?

246
00:12:21,210 --> 00:12:23,200
I am sorry...

247
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:25,050
for what I said.

248
00:12:25,050 --> 00:12:26,150
Truly.

249
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:30,120
♪

250
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:32,080
I said that I was sorry!

251
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:35,250
♪

252
00:12:35,250 --> 00:12:37,000
I know that you're awake!

253
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:39,060
Say something, Mr. Wanderer!

254
00:12:39,060 --> 00:12:41,060
♪

255
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,250
Mr. Wanderer?

256
00:12:42,250 --> 00:12:46,220
♪

257
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:48,050
Whoa.

258
00:12:48,050 --> 00:12:54,170
♪

259
00:12:54,170 --> 00:12:57,170
(wind blowing)

260
00:12:57,170 --> 00:13:12,070
♪

261
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:14,270
Why didn't I
at least ask his name?

262
00:13:16,140 --> 00:13:18,000
Wanderer.

263
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:22,070
Wow, he's amazing
with just his left arm!

264
00:13:22,070 --> 00:13:24,090
You obliterated
that thing, Gohei.

265
00:13:24,090 --> 00:13:26,210
Uh, I mean, uh, Battousai.

266
00:13:26,210 --> 00:13:27,180
Sensei Battousai,

267
00:13:27,180 --> 00:13:29,210
are you testing your
sword again tonight?

268
00:13:29,210 --> 00:13:31,050
Yes, I am, it is time.

269
00:13:31,050 --> 00:13:33,100
-So, are you ready?
-You bet.

270
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:36,080
Yeah, someone's gonna pay for
this useless thumb I can't use!

271
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:38,200
(yelling)

272
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:40,140
(screaming)

273
00:13:40,140 --> 00:13:42,250
-Oh my God, he's bleeding.
-Are you all right?

274
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:44,260
So who else thinks
they can take me?

275
00:13:44,260 --> 00:13:47,080
(groaning)

276
00:13:47,080 --> 00:13:48,290
Kori, stay back.

277
00:13:51,180 --> 00:13:52,280
(all gasping)

278
00:13:52,280 --> 00:13:54,010
-Sensei!
-Sensei!

279
00:13:54,010 --> 00:13:55,200
-Hiruma!
-Hm?

280
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,200
Why did you break the rules?

281
00:13:57,200 --> 00:13:59,180
I told you not to hurt people.

282
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:02,130
That is the essence
of being a Kamiya sensei.

283
00:14:02,130 --> 00:14:04,160
I don't wanna take
lessons from you anymore.

284
00:14:04,160 --> 00:14:07,010
A sword is made for cutting.

285
00:14:07,010 --> 00:14:09,110
This sword is hungry
to taste some flesh.

286
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:10,200
Ah!

287
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,120
Just like yours.

288
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:14,090
(yelling)

289
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:22,040
(growling)

290
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:24,020
It's too bad you won't
be able to hold a sword

291
00:14:24,020 --> 00:14:26,070
with that hand anymore, Hiruma.

292
00:14:28,080 --> 00:14:30,110
You...

293
00:14:30,110 --> 00:14:32,070
You are expelled.

294
00:14:32,070 --> 00:14:35,000
And don't ever come back
to this dojo again.

295
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,240
(laughing)

296
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,120
(whimpering)

297
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,260
♪

298
00:14:41,260 --> 00:14:43,080
(laughing diabolically)

299
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:44,050
(gasps)

300
00:14:49,010 --> 00:14:51,120
(sighs)

301
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:54,080
I remember.

302
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:57,000
The guy whose
right thumb got slashed.

303
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:04,704
♪

304
00:15:04,704 --> 00:15:05,230
It's here.

305
00:15:05,230 --> 00:15:08,240
He was expelled 11 years ago.

306
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,280
Hiruma Gohei.

307
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:12,000
(door opens)

308
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:14,180
♪

309
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,170
(laughing)

310
00:15:16,170 --> 00:15:19,040
So it was you after all!

311
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,200
Yeah, you finally remembered me.

312
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:24,190
For the past 11 years,
I've been waiting for this day

313
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:26,060
so I could destroy this place

314
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:29,100
and send the Kamiya
Kasshin style to hell!

315
00:15:29,100 --> 00:15:31,130
Revenge is why you
slandered my father

316
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:32,290
with your street murders!

317
00:15:32,290 --> 00:15:34,080
♪

318
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,150
Thanks to your father,
I have trained my left hand

319
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,260
for 11 years.

320
00:15:37,260 --> 00:15:39,080
Oh, and I would
love to show him

321
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:43,170
how good my left-handed
killing skills really are.

322
00:15:43,170 --> 00:15:44,220
(panting)

323
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:48,030
My father's Kasshin style
will not be defeated by you!

324
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:49,070
(yelling)

325
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:51,240
♪

326
00:15:51,240 --> 00:15:53,160
It would be useless.

327
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:57,030
(gasping)

328
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,250
(grunting)

329
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:01,040
My revenge will be
complete when I bury you

330
00:16:01,040 --> 00:16:02,230
and destroy this dojo.

331
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:04,260
I will send you to hell slowly!

332
00:16:04,260 --> 00:16:07,070
First I will make
you kiss my feet.

333
00:16:07,070 --> 00:16:08,240
But what do you think,
should I let you guys

334
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:11,000
have slashing practice first?

335
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,040
Yes, let me do it.

336
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,090
-Me too.
-And me!

337
00:16:13,090 --> 00:16:15,130
But a sword is supposed
to protect people.

338
00:16:15,130 --> 00:16:16,180
Yeah, right!

339
00:16:16,180 --> 00:16:19,290
(laughing)

340
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:23,060
Well, cutie, too bad there's
no sword to protect you now.

341
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:25,030
(grunting)

342
00:16:29,190 --> 00:16:32,040
(yelling, gasping)

343
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,170
What?

344
00:16:33,170 --> 00:16:37,020
What is it, Nishiwaki?

345
00:16:37,020 --> 00:16:40,050
I tried to...

346
00:16:40,050 --> 00:16:42,200
(grunts)

347
00:16:42,200 --> 00:16:44,100
Ah, Wanderer.

348
00:16:44,100 --> 00:16:46,130
You better let her go right now.

349
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:49,030
Hey, you're that guy
from yesterday!

350
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:50,250
I guess I should have
taken care of you

351
00:16:50,250 --> 00:16:52,150
when I had the chance.

352
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:56,030
Wanderer, you're
no match for this guy!

353
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:57,200
Do you also believe
that the sword

354
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:59,200
is there to protect people?

355
00:16:59,200 --> 00:17:00,210
No.

356
00:17:00,210 --> 00:17:03,090
♪

357
00:17:03,090 --> 00:17:06,110
I believe a sword is a weapon.

358
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:09,220
And the real truth is...

359
00:17:09,220 --> 00:17:11,280
kendo is a technique for murder.

360
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:14,200
♪

361
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:17,120
You see, Ms. Kori thinks
the I am a harmless man

362
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:18,280
and that I could
never kill anyone,

363
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:22,040
even if it was for
the good of others.

364
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:24,080
How I love her
naive perception of me

365
00:17:24,080 --> 00:17:25,160
and I wish it were the truth,

366
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:27,150
but I'm afraid that it isn't.

367
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:28,270
Oh!

368
00:17:28,270 --> 00:17:30,160
So, how many of you
want to get to know

369
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:33,090
the real me?

370
00:17:33,090 --> 00:17:34,110
(growling)

371
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:37,070
Go get that little twerp
and torture him right now!

372
00:17:37,070 --> 00:17:38,150
(grunting, muttering)

373
00:17:38,150 --> 00:17:39,130
Run!

374
00:17:39,130 --> 00:17:41,210
Stay back, I don't
want to hurt anyone.

375
00:17:41,210 --> 00:17:43,150
Well, it won't
be us getting hurt.

376
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:45,150
Just your death.

377
00:17:45,150 --> 00:17:47,150
(yelling)

378
00:17:47,150 --> 00:17:59,000
♪

379
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,280
(grunting)

380
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:01,290
How'd he do that?

381
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:03,290
He takes out four to
five people with one swing!

382
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:05,140
It's magic!

383
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:07,010
No, he's just quick.

384
00:18:07,010 --> 00:18:09,070
He anticipates your every move.

385
00:18:09,070 --> 00:18:13,130
♪

386
00:18:13,130 --> 00:18:17,040
Red hair and that cross
there on his cheek.

387
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:19,240
Why, this guy, he's--he's...

388
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:21,170
I forgot to tell them.

389
00:18:21,170 --> 00:18:23,260
The technique used
by Battousai the Slasher

390
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:25,260
is neither the
Kamiya Kasshin style

391
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:27,040
or self-taught.

392
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,240
It's Hiten Mitsurugi style.

393
00:18:28,240 --> 00:18:31,250
It utilizes a killer sword
combined with the speed of God

394
00:18:31,250 --> 00:18:34,110
which slaughters everyone
who stands in its way.

395
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:36,240
You mean to tell me
you are the real Slasher?

396
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,220
Oh my!

397
00:18:37,220 --> 00:18:39,040
(gasps)

398
00:18:39,040 --> 00:18:40,200
That's very interesting.

399
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:42,290
We don't need two
of us, now do we?

400
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:46,170
I'm the only one who deserves
to be called Battousai.

401
00:18:46,170 --> 00:18:50,010
If I kill you, then
I'll be the strongest!

402
00:18:50,010 --> 00:18:51,270
So this is it then.

403
00:18:51,270 --> 00:18:54,130
Die, Battousai!

404
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:56,270
-Up here.
-Huh?

405
00:18:56,270 --> 00:18:57,150
Ah!

406
00:18:57,150 --> 00:18:59,120
(yelling)

407
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:10,020
I don't have any affection
for the name "Battousai,"

408
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:11,120
you know?

409
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:15,040
But I...I sure wasn't
gonna let that idiot use it.

410
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:17,230
Of course, he couldn't hold a
sword in his right hand anyway

411
00:19:17,230 --> 00:19:19,050
with that bad thumb of his.

412
00:19:19,050 --> 00:19:21,000
Unbelievable,
this guy's amazing.

413
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:22,270
He took these guys
out singlehanded

414
00:19:22,270 --> 00:19:23,260
and they're still alive!

415
00:19:23,260 --> 00:19:25,040
Would you please
go get the police

416
00:19:25,040 --> 00:19:26,290
and tell them what
this guy has done?

417
00:19:26,290 --> 00:19:27,280
And could you move it?

418
00:19:27,280 --> 00:19:30,000
Yes, sir, yes, sir!

419
00:19:34,020 --> 00:19:36,000
♪

420
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:38,040
I'm very sorry,
Ms. Kori, really.

421
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:39,170
I didn't want
to hide it from you.

422
00:19:39,170 --> 00:19:41,000
It's just...

423
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,200
♪

424
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,170
I guess I didn't want
you to know about it

425
00:19:44,170 --> 00:19:46,200
or want to frighten you.

426
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,050
(sighs)

427
00:19:48,050 --> 00:19:49,270
♪

428
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:51,020
Farewell.

429
00:19:51,020 --> 00:19:52,280
♪

430
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,030
But...

431
00:19:54,030 --> 00:19:55,270
wait!

432
00:19:55,270 --> 00:19:57,220
-Wait!
-Ah!

433
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:59,070
You're not just going
to leave, are you?

434
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:00,190
Wait a second, let's talk.

435
00:20:00,190 --> 00:20:04,160
How can I revive the
Kasshin style all by myself?

436
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:06,120
Why don't you help me a little?

437
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:08,050
I told you I don't
care about your past

438
00:20:08,050 --> 00:20:09,250
or what you've done before.

439
00:20:09,250 --> 00:20:12,090
But after the news of this
Battousai imposter spreads,

440
00:20:12,090 --> 00:20:13,280
if I remained here,
then all the effort

441
00:20:13,280 --> 00:20:16,180
we put into restoring
your dojo will be lost.

442
00:20:16,180 --> 00:20:19,110
I never said that I wanted
Battousai to remain here.

443
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:21,210
I want you, the
Wanderer, to stay here.

444
00:20:21,210 --> 00:20:24,220
Oh!

445
00:20:24,220 --> 00:20:27,230
Well, if you insist on leaving,

446
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:30,000
you could at least
tell me your name.

447
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Not the name of
some legendary slasher

448
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:33,160
or any other nickname you have,

449
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:35,010
just your real name.

450
00:20:35,010 --> 00:20:36,000
Himura.

451
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:37,140
It's Kenshin Himura.

452
00:20:37,140 --> 00:20:39,010
♪

453
00:20:39,010 --> 00:20:40,210
Kenshin.

454
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:42,240
Kenshin, I'm sorry you must go.

455
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,030
(door closes)

456
00:20:44,030 --> 00:20:45,110
Oh!

457
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:47,180
(sighs)

458
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:50,100
I'm a little tired of traveling.

459
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:56,010
♪

460
00:20:56,010 --> 00:20:58,210
I feel like staying put
for a little while.

461
00:20:58,210 --> 00:21:00,060
♪

462
00:21:00,060 --> 00:21:02,050
And you said you
liked my cooking.

463
00:21:02,050 --> 00:21:04,050
Well, you're a much
better cook than I am.

464
00:21:04,050 --> 00:21:06,220
I hope I don't accidentally
see you in the bath again!

465
00:21:06,220 --> 00:21:07,240
Well, that's all right

466
00:21:07,240 --> 00:21:09,280
'cause if you ever do...

467
00:21:09,280 --> 00:21:13,080
(groaning)

468
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:15,280
Oh no, I thought you
were going to avoid it!

469
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:19,050
That ox sure has
one heck of a kick.

470
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:22,160
♪

471
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,270
Now, don't move your jaw.

472
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:26,010
But it hurts!

473
00:21:26,010 --> 00:21:26,534
Baby!

474
00:21:26,534 --> 00:21:28,030
Baby!

475
00:21:28,030 --> 00:21:31,090
♪

476
00:21:31,090 --> 00:21:33,070
And that's how
Kenshin the Wanderer

477
00:21:33,070 --> 00:21:36,000
joined our Kamiya dojo.

478
00:21:37,120 --> 00:21:49,130
♪

479
00:21:49,130 --> 00:21:51,130
(singing in foreign language)

480
00:21:51,130 --> 00:23:16,170
♪

